        <content><![CDATA[ <h1 class="title topictitle1">Service catalog properties</h1>  <div class="body conbody">  <p class="p">You can control the behavior of your Service Catalog using the properties that are made   available to you.</p>  <p class="p">The <span class="ph menucascade"><span class="ph uicontrol">Catalog Variables</span> &gt; <span class="ph uicontrol">Variable Default Size </span></span> submodule lets you configure the default width size for variables in all catalog   forms. The options include:</p>  <ul class="ul" id="zz_system_properties_ui-normal__ul_py1_jnx_rz"><li class="li">25%: Configures the variable to occupy 25% of the available screen size.</li><li class="li">50%: Configures the variable to occupy 50% of the available screen size.</li><li class="li">75%: Configures the variable to occupy 75% of the available screen size.</li><li class="li">100%: Configures the variable to occupy 100% of the available screen size.</li></ul>  <p class="p">You can override the default width of a variable. To do so, customize the width size of a   variable under <span class="ph uicontrol">Type Specifications</span> in the Variable form. </p> </div> <div class="related-links"><div class="relinfo"><div class="reltitle">Related information<br /><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Service-Catalog-Properties&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Service Catalog properties</a></div><div><a class="link" href="https://docs.servicenow.com/?context&#61;CSHelp:Configure-Default-Variable-Width&amp;version&#61;kingston" target="_blank">Configure a default width for service catalog variables</a></div></div></div></div>]]></content>
